Trials of safe standing at football grounds moved a step closer after a survey of fans across the country revealed that 96 per cent backed its return.

The campaign to see standing in the terraces introduced back into English football has been gathering pace.

Last year, Manchester United chief executive Ed Woodward pledged to support the principle of having safe standing at Old Trafford, as revealed by Sportsmail.

