That followed a number of Premier League clubs, including Aston Villa, Hull and Swansea, indicating their support for the idea.

Now a survey of 2,364 fans from around the country, conducted by the Welsh Conservatives and the Football Supporters Federation, has confirmed that the majority would like to see it trialled in stadiums.

The survey also suggested that 84 per cent believe it would decrease problems between stewards and fans and 97 per cent feel that modern technology can make standing safe at grounds.

