Director of Communications for the Football Supporters Federation Michael Brunskill said: ‘Many fans love to stand at games, it can vastly improve the atmosphere and camaraderie at games, it's only natural to stand when you sing.

‘Safe standing areas exist on the continent and the FSF believes they should be introduced into our grounds as well. These areas are modern and safe, a million miles from the crumbling death traps of the 80s.

‘It's fantastic to see fans, clubs, and politicians coming together to deliver this message to Westminster. We need a safe standing pilot - and why shouldn't that be in Wales?’ Standing areas at football grounds in the Premier League and Championship has been outlawed since 1994 at the recommendation of the Taylor Report on the Hillsborough disaster which claimed the lives of 96 Liverpool supporters.

 

